==Old English==

===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*rēda-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[red|rēd]], Old Saxon [[rad|rād]] (Dutch [[raad]] ‘advice’), Old High German [[rat|rāt]] (German [[Rat]] ‘advice’), Old Norse [[ráð]] (Swedish [[råd]] ‘advice, way out’).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ræ:d/

===Noun===
'''rǣd''' {{m}}

# [[help]], [[advice]], [[counsel]]
# [[decision]], a [[plan]]
# [[judgement]], [[reason]]

===Related terms===
*[[rædan|rǣdan]] (English [[read]])

===Descendents===
*English [[rede]]

